begin_memory_text: We talked about running, sports, and the Olympics. I mentioned I was doing fantasy football which was why I was watching football while he mentioned he used to do fantasy running and we connected on running cross country and track.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the comedian Bill Burr and the perceived grievances of white women in his joke while I blathered on about white women having no standing on intersectional grievance against a lot of other minorities.
end_memory_text: We talked about our geographical locations. Him in Montgomery County, MD, and me in Vienna, VA. We talked about upstate New York where he went to school at Cornell and myself at UVA.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week might go ok. I don't have too much in terms of expectations, but I do think the work aspect will be somewhat busy. I hope I'll find time to get in some running outside if the weather is ok. I may try to see if there are any events occurring.
critical_positive: I think the thing that worked well was that we were both part of the professional class. We were both relatively close in age. We also both were located fairly close to each other in geographic location. We had some similarities around interests primarily with regards to running and an interest in the Olympics.
critical_negative: I think I blathered on a bit more than I should have. I went on a tangent to something he brought up and sort of made it all about me. I think I may have went slightly political when I should not have. I also think I dominated the conversation slightly when I should not have.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning, we discussed sports - particularly running, some martial arts, and then the Olympics. He is interested in spectating martial arts and had plans to go to the Toyko Olympics next year.
middle_memory_text: The middle of the conversation was more about politics - particularly race and culture. My Asian conversation partner expressed his views related to Asian history's influence of education on the present focus of Asians (and Asian-Americans) promoting education.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation, we were talking about places - particularly that we both are from the DMV area, where he grew up, the state of California (no pun intended), and where I grew up.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going okay. Not particularly good and not particularly bad. I have a lot to do both at work and outside of work, but the weather is throwing a curve ball to me because it makes my exercise more complicate. Running now requires more planning because of the significant swings in temperature in my region.
critical_positive: I liked that he talked a lot because I didn't have to worry as much to think of conversation topics or how I would respond. In addition, I was genuinely curious about the Olympics and I thought it was cool that my conversation partner planned on going to the Tokyo Olympics next year.
critical_negative: If I had to choose, I felt a bit awkward to hear the conflicting political opinions. I didn't want to be antagonistic and I genuinely wasn't prepared for a conversation like that so I mostly kept quiet and agreed (or gave a passive answer to not agree with him, but not contradict either).
